The paper focuses on the performance of the Mobility Management Entity (MME) in cellular networks with support for IoT, specifically in terms of delay and control traffic. This topic is closely related to network infrastructure (NI) and communication and networking (CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses virtualized networks and the efficient allocation of computing resources, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC) sub-category. The need for effective scaling decisions also suggests a systems and control (SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents closed-form expressions and analysis, which could also fall under the information theory (IT) sub-category.
